! {{{label|}}}
{{!}} {{{value|}}}|}}</includeonly><noinclude>
Renders one property row in a SemanticSchemas display table:

 |-
 ! label
 | value

Skipped entirely when `value` is empty — callers don't need to guard.

This is the building block Category/table and Category/sidebox use for
each baked property. Compose it directly in hand-written custom display
templates:

 {| class="wikitable"
 {{Category/property-row | label=Title | value={{{has_title|}}} }}
 {{Category/property-row | label=Author | value={{Property/Page | value={{{has_author|}}} }} }}
 |}

Parameters:
* label - Display label for the row (left column).
* value - Rendered value expression (right column). Pass a formatted
          string or the output of Property/Page, Property/Email, etc.
          If empty, the whole row is suppressed.
</noinclude>
